            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EJesus%20promised%20that%20the%20Holy%20Spirit%20would%20convict%20the%20world%20of%20guilt%20in%20regard%20to%20sin.%20Conviction%20arises%20from%20confrontation%20with%20evidence.%20The%20Holy%20Spirit%20is%20the%20Spirit%20of%20truth%2C%20and%20He%20holds%20before%20your%20conscience%20the%20evidence%20of%20your%20sin%2C%20leaving%20you%20no%20room%20for%20escape.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20prophet%20Nathan%20confronted%20David%20with%20a%20parable%20that%20illustrated%20David's%20guilt%20with%20Bathsheba%20(2%20Samuel%2012%3A7).%20The%20simple%20parable%20smote%20his%20conscience%2C%20and%20David%20truly%20repented%20from%20his%20heart.%20Although%20his%20sin%20was%20great%2C%20he%20received%20forgiveness%20because%20his%20repentance%20was%20genuine.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWhen%20God%20confronts%20you%20with%20the%20truth%20of%20your%20sin%2C%20He%20is%20showing%20mercy.%20As%20Jesus%20said%2C%20%22And%20you%20will%20know%20the%20truth%2C%20and%20the%20truth%20will%20set%20you%20free%22%20(John%208%3A32).%20Never%20run%20from%20the%20evidence.%20The%20Holy%20Spirit%20will%20bring%20certain%20scriptures%20to%20you%20as%20a%20mirror%20to%20show%20you%20your%20true%20self.%20If%20you%20respond%20to%20His%20mercy%20and%20grace%2C%20you%20will%20be%20set%20free%20from%20whatever%20sin%20has%20plagued%20you.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EInvite%20the%20Holy%20Spirit%20to%20shine%20the%20light%20on%20the%20truth%20of%20your%20life%20and%20actions.%20Then%20honestly%20accept%20and%20admit%20His%20evidence%2C%20and%20confess%20with%20David%2C%20%22I%20have%20sinned%20against%20the%20Lord%22%20(2%20Samuel%2012%3A13).%20Then%2C%20and%20only%20then%2C%20will%20you%20hear%20Him%20say%2C%20%22Yes%2C%20but%20the%20Lord%20has%20forgiven%20you%22%20(v.%2013).%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
            "id": "ot-passage",
