            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "2Samuel.12:1-31",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3E2%20Samuel%2012%3A1-31%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_12_1%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E2%20Samuel%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3ENathan%20Rebukes%20David%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20sent%20Nathan%20the%20prophet%20to%20tell%20David%20this%20story%3A%20%26%23x201C%3BThere%20were%20two%20men%20in%20a%20certain%20town.%20One%20was%20rich%2C%20and%20one%20was%20poor.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_12_2%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20rich%20man%20owned%20a%20great%20many%20sheep%20and%20cattle.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_12_3%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20poor%20man%20owned%20nothing%20but%20one%20little%20lamb%20he%20had%20bought.%20He%20raised%20that%20little%20lamb%2C%20and%20it%20grew%20up%20with%20his%20children.%20It%20ate%20from%20the%20man%26%23x2019%3Bs%20own%20plate%20and%20drank%20from%20his%20cup.%20He%20cuddled%20it%20in%20his%20arms%20like%20a%20baby%20daughter.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_12_4%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EOne%20day%20a%20guest%20arrived%20at%20the%20home%20of%20the%20rich%20man.%20But%20instead%20of%20killing%20an%20animal%20from%20his%20own%20flock%20or%20herd%2C%20he%20took%20the%20poor%20man%26%23x2019%3Bs%20lamb%20and%20killed%20it%20and%20prepared%20it%20for%20his%20guest.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_12_5%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EDavid%20was%20furious.%20%26%23x201C%3BAs%20surely%20as%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20lives%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20he%20vowed%2C%20%26%23x201C%3Bany%20man%20who%20would%20do%20such%20a%20thing%20deserves%20to%20die!%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_12_6%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20must%20repay%20four%20lambs%20to%20the%20poor%20man%20for%20the%20one%20he%20stole%20and%20for%20having%20no%20pity.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_12_7%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Nathan%20said%20to%20David%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BYou%20are%20that%20man!%20The%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20God%20of%20Israel%2C%20says%3A%20I%20anointed%20you%20king%20of%20Israel%20and%20saved%20you%20from%20the%20power%20of%20Saul.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_12_8%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EI%20gave%20you%20your%20master%26%23x2019%3Bs%20house%20and%20his%20wives%20and%20the%20kingdoms%20of%20Israel%20and%20Judah.%20And%20if%20that%20had%20not%20been%20enough%2C%20I%20would%20have%20given%20you%20much%2C%20much%20more.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_12_9%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EWhy%2C%20then%2C%20have%20you%20despised%20the%20word%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20done%20this%20horrible%20deed%3F%20For%20you%20have%20murdered%20Uriah%20the%20Hittite%20with%20the%20sword%20of%20the%20Ammonites%20and%20stolen%20his%20wife.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_12_10%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EFrom%20this%20time%20on%2C%20your%20family%20will%20live%20by%20the%20sword%20because%20you%20have%20despised%20me%20by%20taking%20Uriah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20wife%20to%20be%20your%20own.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_12_11%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BThis%20is%20what%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20says%3A%20Because%20of%20what%20you%20have%20done%2C%20I%20will%20cause%20your%20own%20household%20to%20rebel%20against%20you.%20I%20will%20give%20your%20wives%20to%20another%20man%20before%20your%20very%20eyes%2C%20and%20he%20will%20go%20to%20bed%20with%20them%20in%20public%20view.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_12_12%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EYou%20did%20it%20secretly%2C%20but%20I%20will%20make%20this%20happen%20to%20you%20openly%20in%20the%20sight%20of%20all%20Israel.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_12_13%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EDavid%20Confesses%20His%20Guilt%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20David%20confessed%20to%20Nathan%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BI%20have%20sinned%20against%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3ENathan%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BYes%2C%20but%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20has%20forgiven%20you%2C%20and%20you%20won%26%23x2019%3Bt%20die%20for%20this%20sin.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_12_14%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3ENevertheless%2C%20because%20you%20have%20shown%20utter%20contempt%20for%20the%20word%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E12%3A14%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20Dead%20Sea%20Scrolls%3B%20Masoretic%20Text%20reads%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20enemies%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ci%20class%3D%22tn-sc-ital%22%3ELord.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20by%20doing%20this%2C%20your%20child%20will%20die.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_12_15%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EAfter%20Nathan%20returned%20to%20his%20home%2C%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20sent%20a%20deadly%20illness%20to%20the%20child%20of%20David%20and%20Uriah%26%23x2019%3Bs%20wife.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_12_16%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EDavid%20begged%20God%20to%20spare%20the%20child.%20He%20went%20without%20food%20and%20lay%20all%20night%20on%20the%20bare%20ground.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_12_17%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20elders%20of%20his%20household%20pleaded%20with%20him%20to%20get%20up%20and%20eat%20with%20them%2C%20but%20he%20refused.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_12_18%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20on%20the%20seventh%20day%20the%20child%20died.%20David%26%23x2019%3Bs%20advisers%20were%20afraid%20to%20tell%20him.%20%26%23x201C%3BHe%20wouldn%26%23x2019%3Bt%20listen%20to%20reason%20while%20the%20child%20was%20ill%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20they%20said.%20%26%23x201C%3BWhat%20drastic%20thing%20will%20he%20do%20when%20we%20tell%20him%20the%20child%20is%20dead%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_12_19%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20David%20saw%20them%20whispering%2C%20he%20realized%20what%20had%20happened.%20%26%23x201C%3BIs%20the%20child%20dead%3F%26%23x201D%3B%20he%20asked.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BYes%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20they%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3Bhe%20is%20dead.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_12_20%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20David%20got%20up%20from%20the%20ground%2C%20washed%20himself%2C%20put%20on%20lotions%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E12%3A20%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Eanointed%20himself.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20changed%20his%20clothes.%20He%20went%20to%20the%20Tabernacle%20and%20worshiped%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20After%20that%2C%20he%20returned%20to%20the%20palace%20and%20was%20served%20food%20and%20ate.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_12_21%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3EHis%20advisers%20were%20amazed.%20%26%23x201C%3BWe%20don%26%23x2019%3Bt%20understand%20you%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20they%20told%20him.%20%26%23x201C%3BWhile%20the%20child%20was%20still%20living%2C%20you%20wept%20and%20refused%20to%20eat.%20But%20now%20that%20the%20child%20is%20dead%2C%20you%20have%20stopped%20your%20mourning%20and%20are%20eating%20again.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_12_22%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3EDavid%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BI%20fasted%20and%20wept%20while%20the%20child%20was%20alive%2C%20for%20I%20said%2C%20%26%23x2018%3BPerhaps%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20will%20be%20gracious%20to%20me%20and%20let%20the%20child%20live.%26%23x2019%3B%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_12_23%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E23%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20why%20should%20I%20fast%20when%20he%20is%20dead%3F%20Can%20I%20bring%20him%20back%20again%3F%20I%20will%20go%20to%20him%20one%20day%2C%20but%20he%20cannot%20return%20to%20me.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_12_24%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E24%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20David%20comforted%20Bathsheba%2C%20his%20wife%2C%20and%20slept%20with%20her.%20She%20became%20pregnant%20and%20gave%20birth%20to%20a%20son%2C%20and%20David%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E12%3A24%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ehe%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20an%20alternate%20Hebrew%20reading%20and%20some%20Hebrew%20manuscripts%20read%20%3Cem%3Eshe.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20named%20him%20Solomon.%20The%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20loved%20the%20child%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam2_12_25%22%20bk%3D%22sam2%22%20ch%3D%2212%22%20vn%3D%2225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E25%3C%2Fspan%3Eand%20sent%20word%20through%20Nathan%20the%20prophet%20that%20they%20should%20name%20him%20Jedidiah%20(which%20means%20%26%23x201C%3Bbeloved%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201D%3B)%2C%20as%20the%20%3Cspan%